    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-03-11T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-03-11T18:00:00-05:00" n="534"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d534">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">393.115/879: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Grew</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-03-11T18:00:00-05:00"
                            >March 11, 1940—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>87. Reference Canton’s telegrams of February 9, 6 p.m., and March 5, 3 p.m.,<note
                        n="69" xml:id="d534fn69">Neither printed.</note> in regard to oil monopoly
                    in Namhoi district. The Department authorizes you in your discretion to make
                    appropriate representations to the Japanese Foreign Office.<note n="70"
                        xml:id="d534fn70">See note No. 1498, March 20, from the American Ambassador
                        in Japan to the Japanese Minister for Foreign Affairs, <ref
                            target="frus1931-41v01#pg_860">
                            <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, Japan, 1931–1941, vol. <hi
                                rend="smallcaps">i</hi>, p. 860</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <p>Sent to Tokyo via Peiping. Repeated to Canton and Chungking.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
